# Run Spotify on native Wayland. The old X11 forcing existed so Mutter would
# draw a normal titlebar (native Wayland showed a plain grey Chromium one) —
# moot under Hyprland, which tiles these borderless, and on a fractional (1.2)
# monitor scale XWayland gets bitmap-upscaled → grainy text. Spotify is CEF, not
# Electron, so ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT does nothing; the wayland socket is
# granted here and `--ozone-platform-hint=auto` is passed at launch instead (see
# applications/com.spotify.Client.desktop and the exec-once in hyprland.nix).
[Context]
sockets=wayland;
